%sql
CREATE TEMPORARY VIEW salary
AS
WITH
tmp (
SELECT
    REPLACE(CompensationAmount, ',', '') * exchangeRate / 0.000886 / 10000 AS salary, -- 원화 만원 단위로 변경
    *
FROM
    survey
    JOIN exchange ON survey.CompensationCurrency = exchange.originCountry
)
SELECT *
FROM tmp
WHERE
    salary IS NOT NULL
    AND salary > 0 AND salary < 100000 -- 연봉이 10억원이상인 자들의 존재를 부정
    AND EmploymentStatus = 'Employed full-time'
    AND Country <> 'Other'

%sql
WITH
target (
SELECT salary AS x
FROM salary
WHERE TRUE ${filter} -- filter가 빈 문자열일때를 위한 의미 없는 TRUE
),
stats (
SELECT
    MIN(x) AS x_min,
    ${num_bins=20} AS num_bins,
    (MAX(x) - MIN(x)) / ${num_bins=20} AS bin_width
FROM target
),
bin_tmp (
SELECT
    x,
    FLOOR((x - x_min) / bin_width) AS bin
FROM target CROSS JOIN stats
),
bin (
SELECT
    x,
    CASE WHEN bin = num_bins THEN num_bins - 1 ELSE bin END AS bin  -- 마지막 bin의 범위를 90 ~ 99이 아닌 90 ~ 100이 되도록
FROM bin_tmp CROSS JOIN stats
)
SELECT
    bin,
    COUNT(*) AS bin_count,
    AVG(x) AS bin_avg,
    MIN(x) AS bin_min,
    MAX(x) AS bin_max,
    MIN(bin_width) * bin AS bin_start,
    MIN(bin_width) * (bin + 1) AS bin_end
FROM bin CROSS JOIN stats
GROUP BY bin
ORDER BY bin

.display

%sql
SELECT
    ${group} AS `그룹`,
    MIN(salary) AS `연봉: 최소`,
    percentile(salary, 0.10) AS `연봉: 하위10%`,
    AVG(salary) AS `연봉: 평균`,
    percentile(salary, 0.5) AS `연봉: 중앙값`,
    percentile(salary, 0.90) AS `연봉: 상위10%`,
    MAX(salary) AS `연봉: 최대`,
    COUNT(*) AS `설문자 수`
FROM salary
WHERE
    ${group} IS NOT NULL
    ${filter}
GROUP BY ${group}
HAVING COUNT(*) > ${minRespon}
ORDER BY 5 DESC

%pyspark
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pyspark.sql import DataFrame

df = DataFrame(z.get("df"), sqlContext).toPandas()

%pyspark
df['MATLABUsers']=[1 if df['WorkToolsFrequencyMATLAB'].iloc[i] in ['Most of the time','Often'] else 0 for i in range(df.shape[0])]
df['AWSUsers']=[1 if df['WorkToolsFrequencyAWS'].iloc[i] in ['Most of the time','Often'] else 0 for i in range(df.shape[0])]
df['HadoopUsers']=[1 if df['WorkToolsFrequencyHadoop'].iloc[i] in ['Most of the time','Often'] else 0 for i in range(df.shape[0])]
df['SparkUsers']=[1 if df['WorkToolsFrequencySpark'].iloc[i] in ['Most of the time','Often'] else 0 for i in range(df.shape[0])]

df['NaiveBayesUsers']=[1 if df['WorkMethodsFrequencyNaiveBayes'].iloc[i] in ['Most of the time','Often'] else 0 for i in range(df.shape[0])]
df['RecommenderSystemsUsers']=[1 if df['WorkMethodsFrequencyRecommenderSystems'].iloc[i] in ['Most of the time','Often'] else 0 for i in range(df.shape[0])]
df['DataVisualizationUsers']=[1 if df['WorkMethodsFrequencyDataVisualization'].iloc[i] in ['Most of the time','Often'] else 0 for i in range(df.shape[0])]

features= ['salary', 'GenderSelect', 'Age', 'FormalEducation', 'MajorSelect', 'ParentsEducation',
           'DataScienceIdentitySelect', 'RemoteWork','WorkMLTeamSeatSelect',
           'Tenure','EmployerIndustry','EmployerSize','CurrentJobTitleSelect','JobFunctionSelect',
           'MATLABUsers','AWSUsers','HadoopUsers','SparkUsers',
           'NaiveBayesUsers','RecommenderSystemsUsers','DataVisualizationUsers',
           'TimeGatheringData','TimeModelBuilding','TimeProduction','TimeVisualizing','TimeFindingInsights']

%pyspark
dataset = df[features]
dataset=pd.get_dummies(dataset,columns=[
    'GenderSelect', 'FormalEducation','MajorSelect','ParentsEducation',
    'DataScienceIdentitySelect','RemoteWork','WorkMLTeamSeatSelect',
    'Tenure','EmployerIndustry','EmployerSize','CurrentJobTitleSelect','JobFunctionSelect'])

%pyspark
dataset = df[features]
dataset = pd.get_dummies(dataset, columns=[
    'GenderSelect', 'FormalEducation','MajorSelect','ParentsEducation',
    'DataScienceIdentitySelect','RemoteWork','WorkMLTeamSeatSelect',
    'Tenure','EmployerIndustry','EmployerSize','CurrentJobTitleSelect','JobFunctionSelect'])
    
for col in ['Age','TimeGatheringData','TimeModelBuilding','TimeProduction','TimeVisualizing','TimeFindingInsights']:
    dataset[col] = dataset[col].fillna(value=dataset[col].median())

dataset.dropna(axis=0, inplace=True)

%pyspark
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report

X, y = dataset.drop('salary', axis=1), dataset['salary']
y = (y > 20000).astype('float32')  # 연봉 2억원 이상이면 긍정
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.20, random_state=123)

clf = LogisticRegression(C=0.1).fit(X_train, y_train)

y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)

print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
print("Accuracy: ", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))

%pyspark
coef = pd.DataFrame(data={'column': dataset.columns.tolist()[1:], 'coef': clf.coef_[0].tolist()}).sort_values("coef")
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 20))
sns.barplot(x="coef", y="column", data=coef)
plt.tight_layout()

%pyspark
features = X_test.columns.tolist()
feature = z.select("Feature", [(f, f) for f in features], features[0])

plt.scatter(X_test[feature], clf.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1], s=4)
